{
  "page": "Blue Fork",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Riverlands.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"The riverlands and the location of the Blue Fork\"><img alt=\"The riverlands and the location of the Blue Fork\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d0/The_Riverlands.png/400px-The_Riverlands.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d0/The_Riverlands.png/600px-The_Riverlands.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d0/The_Riverlands.png/800px-The_Riverlands.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 42.2%; left: 32.8%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -5px; top: -5px; width: 10px; font-size: 10px;\"><img alt=\"The riverlands and the location of the Blue Fork\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/10px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Blue Fork\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/15px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/20px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size: 90%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; top:-0.15em; left: -3em; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\"><b>Blue Fork</b></span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">The <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and the location of the Blue Fork\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><table>\n\n<tbody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Blue Fork</b> is one of the three main rivers of the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>, the other two being the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_Fork\" title=\"Green Fork\">Green Fork</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Fork\" title=\"Red Fork\">Red Fork</a>. The Blue Fork is named for the purity of its waters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Course\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Course</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Course\">Course</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Course\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Blue Fork has its source in pure springs<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and marshy terrain south of <a href=\"/index.php/Seagard\" title=\"Seagard\">Seagard</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In order to get around the Blue Fork when it swells its banks, one must travel through <a href=\"/index.php/Sevenstreams\" title=\"Sevenstreams\">Sevenstreams</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Hag%27s_Mire\" title=\"Hag&#39;s Mire\">Hag's Mire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Blue Fork flows to the southeast past <a href=\"/index.php/Oldstones\" title=\"Oldstones\">Oldstones</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Fairmarket\" title=\"Fairmarket\">Fairmarket</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsford\" title=\"Ramsford\">Ramsford</a>, and it meets the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_Fork\" title=\"Green Fork\">Green Fork</a> north of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Harroway%27s_Town\" title=\"Lord Harroway&#39;s Town\">Lord Harroway's Town</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a> then flows into the <a href=\"/index.php/Bay_of_Crabs\" title=\"Bay of Crabs\">Bay of Crabs</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:452px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/76/Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg/450px-Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"221\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/76/Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg/675px-Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/76/Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg/900px-Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Simonetti_Storm_King_Arrek_watches_the_battle_near_the_town_of_fairground.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Arrec_Durrandon\" title=\"Arrec Durrandon\">Arrec Durrandon</a> watches the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Fairmarket\" title=\"Battle at Fairmarket\">battle at Fairmarket</a>, by Marc Simonetti ©</div></div></div>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Tristifer_IV_Mudd\" title=\"Tristifer IV Mudd\">Tristifer IV Mudd</a>, the Hammer of Justice, ruled from a castle, now called <a href=\"/index.php/Oldstones\" title=\"Oldstones\">Oldstones</a>, which overlooked the Blue Fork.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to a semi-canon source, the blue in the sigil of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Strong\" title=\"House Strong\">House Strong</a> referred to the Blue Fork.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_Hoare\" title=\"Harwyn Hoare\">Harwyn Hoare</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"King of the Iron Islands\">King of the Iron Islands</a>, began his conquest of the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> by landing one hundred longships south of <a href=\"/index.php/Seagard\" title=\"Seagard\">Seagard</a> and marching them overland to the Blue Fork. His <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> then used rivers to conquer the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm King</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Arrec_Durrandon\" title=\"Arrec Durrandon\">Arrec Durrandon</a>, with their greatest victory being the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Fairmarket\" title=\"Battle at Fairmarket\">battle at Fairmarket</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The wooden bridge across the Blue Fork at <a href=\"/index.php/Fairmarket\" title=\"Fairmarket\">Fairmarket</a> is newer and larger than a bridge near Oldstones.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Pate_of_the_Blue_Fork\" title=\"Pate of the Blue Fork\">Pate of the Blue Fork</a> takes his title from the river.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After departing the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a>, the army of <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> sweeps around the headwaters of the Blue Fork and travels to the <a href=\"/index.php/Whispering_Wood\" title=\"Whispering Wood\">Whispering Wood</a>. Robb's host is joined by small <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_knight\" title=\"Hedge knight\">hedge knights</a>, and masterless <a href=\"/index.php/Men-at-arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Men-at-arms\">men-at-arms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Robb's army travels north from <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> toward the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a> for the wedding of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Roslin_Frey\" title=\"Roslin Frey\">Roslin Frey</a>. The Blue Fork is flooding its banks, however, with rising waters washing out the bridges at <a href=\"/index.php/Fairmarket\" title=\"Fairmarket\">Fairmarket</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Oldstones\" title=\"Oldstones\">Oldstones</a>. When <a href=\"/index.php/Galbart_Glover\" title=\"Galbart Glover\">Galbart Glover</a> and two others try to cross at <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsford\" title=\"Ramsford\">Ramsford</a>, two horses and one man are drowned and Galbart clings to a rock until being rescued. Robb's host thus rides around the Blue Fork, passing the ruins of Oldstones, rills and brooks near <a href=\"/index.php/Sevenstreams\" title=\"Sevenstreams\">Sevenstreams</a>, and the bogs of <a href=\"/index.php/Hag%27s_Mire\" title=\"Hag&#39;s Mire\">Hag's Mire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Following the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Merrett_Frey\" title=\"Merrett Frey\">Merrett Frey</a> rides to Oldstones to ransom his kinsman <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Frey\" title=\"Petyr Frey\">Petyr</a>, but both Freys are killed by the <a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_banners\" title=\"Brotherhood without banners\">brotherhood without banners</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Lucias_Vypren\" title=\"Lucias Vypren\">Lucias Vypren</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Ryman)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Ryman)\">Black Walder Frey</a> hunt the outlaws of the brotherhood along the Blue Fork.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>All the way up the Blue Fork they rode, past <a href=\"/index.php/Sevenstreams\" title=\"Sevenstreams\">Sevenstreams</a> where the river unraveled into a confusion of rills and brooks, then through <a href=\"/index.php/Hag%27s_Mire\" title=\"Hag&#39;s Mire\">Hag's Mire</a>, where glistening green pools waited to swallow the unwary and the soft ground sucked at the hooves of their horses like a hungry babe at its mother's breast.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Blue_Fork&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Riverlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <